en_144262_0	The National Water Supply and Drainage Board request the public to consume drinking water only for essential purposes.
en_144262_1	The water levels of reservoirs in the Western, Southern, Uva and North-central provinces have dropped due to the prevailing dry weather condition.
en_144262_2	The weather has also increased the water consumption among the consumers.
en_144262_3	The water board further noted that water is supplied via bowsers to residents of areas facing water crisis.
en_144262_4	Accordingly, the General Manager of the Water Board Asoka Kumararatne requests the public to consume drinking water sparingly.
